subroutine stsld(star,cphi2,sphi2,sigzs,nsli,calpha,salpha)
Makes longitudinal position of the strong slice for all slices. Arguments:
• star - Strong beam coordinates
• cphi2 - Cosine crossing angle (Note: same as cphi)
• sphi2 - Sine crossing angle (Note: same as sphi)
• sigzs - RMS bunch length (known as sigz in other places)
• nsli - Number of slices
• calpha - Cosine crossing plane angle
• salpha - Sine crossing plane angle
subroutine boost(np,sphi,cphi,tphi,salpha,calpha,track)
BOOST Lorentz Boost Operation. P,Q,E are all normalized by P0. Arguments:
• star - Strong beam coordinates
• cphi - Cosine crossing angle
• sphi - Sine crossing angle
• tphi - Tanget crossing plane angle
• salpha - Sine crossing plane angle
• calpha - Cosine crossing plane angle
• track - Weak beam coordinates
subroutine sbc(np,star,cphi,nsli,f,ibtyp,ibb,bcu,track,ibbc)
SBC - Synchro-Beam for headon collision. Call BBF (table) disabled. Arguments:
• np - Number of particles tracked
• star - Weak beam coordinates
• cphi - Cosine crossing angle
• nsli - Number of slices of the strong beam
• f - Strength of a slice (calculated as param(ne,4)/dble(nsli), where param is the same as
parbe)
• ibtyp - Switch to turn on fast beam-beam algorithm (0: off, 1: on)
• ibb
• bcu
• track - Weak beam coordinates
• ibbc - Switch to turn on linear coupling (0: off, 1: on)
subroutine boosti(np,sphi,cphi,tphi,salpha,calpha,track)
BOOSTI - inverse Lorentz boost. Arguments:
• np - Number of particles tracked
• sphi - Sine crossing angle
• cphi - Cosine crossing angle
• tphi - Tanget crossing angle
• salpha - Sine crossing plane angle
• calpha - Cosine crossing plane angle
• track - Weak beam coordinates
